wpoints.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aArab Spring, 2010- - Public opinion. 0aArab Spring, 2010-xPublic opinion. 0aCommunication in politicszUnited States. 0aMass media and international relationszUnited States. 0aPolitical oratoryzUnited States. 0aPublic opinionzUnited States. 0aRhetoricxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009xPublic opinion. 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Mass Media. 4aHistory : American History. 4aPolitics and Law : International Relations. 4aPolitics and Law : Presidency, The. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / Executive Branch.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845797040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438457970423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438457970/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles